<font color="#FF0000">CHOOSING FOOD</font><br>
<tt>Tue Aug  5 20:46:18 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art..<br><br>
Without heat there could be no understanding of cold.  Without dry there could be no understanding of wet.  Likewise, good and evil hold up their ends of the continuum on which you and I slide back and forth.<br>
No thought may enter your head without your permission.  It is thoughts that feed the black and white wolf.  What kind of food are you gathering.<br>
I know that it is bad for me to dwell on despairing thoughts.  It is wrong.  I know that it is wrong.. still I do it.<br>
A young man who was troubled decided to climb a tall mountain to pray (the higher you ascend the closer you get to God... not unlike the Tower of Babel.)  In his quest to speak to the Creator, he climbed higher and higher and the air became much cooler than it had been in the hot valley below.  Still, he went higher and became very cold.  He almost stepped on a large rattlesnake.  The snake spoke in a feeble voice, &quot;I am very cold.  I can not move.  Please, take me down the mountain or I will die...&quot;<br>
The young warrior replied, &quot;No, you are a dangerous rattlesnake!&quot;<br>
The snake pleaded and the young warrior decided that he would move the cold-blooded reptile to the warmer floor of the valley.  It would be a good deed.<br>
As he decended the air became warmer and finally very warm as he placed the snake on the hot sand.  The snake struck him in the throat.<br>
As he was dying, he heard the snake say, &quot;You knew what I was when you picked me up!&quot;<br><br>
Hecito Yelo, mita Kola<br><br>
Humming Eagle
